.Dd June 28, 1993
.Dt FSINFO 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm fsinfo
.Nd co-ordinate site-wide filesystem information
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm \&fsinfo
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl a Ar autodir
.Op Fl b Ar bootparams
.Op Fl d Ar dumpsets
.Op Fl e Ar exports
.Op Fl f Ar fstabs
.Op Fl h Ar hostname
.Op Fl m Ar automounts
.Op Fl I Ar dir
.Op Fl D Ar string[=string]]
.Op Fl U Ar string[=string]]
.Ar config ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm fsinfo
utility takes a set of system configuration information, and generates
a co-ordinated set of
.Xr amd ,
.Xr mount
and
.Xr mountd
configuration files.
.Pp
The
.Nm fsinfo
command is fully described in the document
.%T "Amd - The 4.4BSD Automounter"
.Sh "SEE ALSO"
.Xr amd 8 ,
.Xr mount 8 ,
.Xr mountd 8 .
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm fsinfo
command first appeared in 4.4BSD.
